                <div class="script-line you">
                    <div class="script-speaker you">YOU:</div>
                    <p>"Let me make sure I understand both positions. Sales—you need something that makes Johnson viable by Q2. Engineering—you're saying the full multi-tenant architecture can't ship in 3 months. Both of those can be true. The question is whether there's a middle path. What does Johnson actually need to move forward?"</p>
                    <div class="script-annotation">Reframe from "who's right" to "what's the actual problem." Break the impasse by getting specific.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="script-line them">
                    <div class="script-speaker them">SALES:</div>
                    <p>"They need to keep their data separate from other customers. Security requirement."</p>
                </div>

                <div class="script-line you">
                    <div class="script-speaker you">YOU:</div>
                    <p>"Data isolation. Is that the same as full multi-tenant, or is that a subset of the problem?"</p>
